solutions.content:
**Intuition**


lets suppose are at ith index.

suppose we are at index i and with j carpets
dp[i][j] denotes minimum number of uncovered white cells from 0 to i with j 
carpets.

1. if number of carpets = 0 dp[i][j] = number of carpets from 0 to i.


suppose we are at index i and with j carpets
1. we dont put carpet. in this case number of uncovered white cells will be 
number of uncovered white cells at i-1 +  1 (if ith cell is )
dp[i][j]  = dp[i-1][j] + 1 if ith carpet is red;


2. if we are placing carpet (j>0) such that ith is the last cell covered.

i-carpetlength < 0 that means we are fulling covering from 0 to i.
[i][j] = 0

i-carpetlength >= 0 that means we are covering from
i-carpetlength+1 to i and number of carpet left are j-1

so dp[i][j] = dp[i-carpetlength][j-1] // cells i-carpetlength+1 to i is covered

at last we will take minimmum of both the values 
dp[i][j]  = min(dp[i-1][j]) + 1 if ith carpet is red, 0 if i-carpetlength < 0 else dp[i-carpetlength][j-1]

```
class Solution {
public:
    int minimumWhiteTiles(string floor, int numCarpets, int carpetLen) {
        int n = floor.size();
        vector<vector<int>>dp(n,vector<int>(numCarpets+1));
        int ans = 0;
        vector<int>freq(n);
        for(int i = 0;i<n;i++)
        {
            ans += floor[i]-'0';
            freq[i] = ans;
        }
        for(int i = 0;i<n;i++)
        {
            for(int j = 0;j<=numCarpets;j++)
            {
                if(j == 0)
                {
                    dp[i][j] = freq[i];
                    continue;
                }
                if(i-carpetLen < 0)
                {
                    dp[i][j] = 0;
                }
                else if(i-carpetLen >= 0)
                {
                    dp[i][j] = dp[i-carpetLen][j-1];
                }
                int value = 0;
                if(i>0)
                {
                        value += floor[i]-'0';
                      dp[i][j] = min(dp[i-1][j] + value ,dp[i][j]);
                }
                else
                {
                      value += floor[i]-'0';
                    dp[i][j] = min(value ,dp[i][j]);
                }
          }

        }
        return dp[n-1][numCarpets];
    }
};
```

