# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Dynamic Programming take and not take simple intuition.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Solved using Dynamic Programming approach.
There are 3 case , starting from the first tile 
1. Black tile : skip and move to next tile
2. White tile not Take : skip and move to next tile
3. White tile take : use the carpet to cover and move to (curr tile + carpetLen - 1 )th tile
then take the max of all.
We are taking max because we have to find min uncovered tile, so max covered tile. 

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(floor.length() * numCarpets)

- Space complexity:
O(floor.length() * numCarpets)

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:

    int f(int i, int num, int &len, vector<int> &prefix_floor, string &floor,int &n,vector<vector<int>> &dp){
        if(i>=n || num==0) return 0;
        if(dp[i][num]!=-1) return dp[i][num];
        if(floor[i]=='0') return dp[i][num] = f(i+1,num,len,prefix_floor,floor,n,dp);
        int notTake =  f(i+1,num,len,prefix_floor,floor,n,dp);
        int bnd = min(i+len-1,n-1);
        int white = prefix_floor[bnd];
        if(i!=0) white = white - prefix_floor[i-1];
        int take = white + f(i+len,num-1,len,prefix_floor,floor,n,dp);
        return dp[i][num] = max(take,notTake);
    }

    int minimumWhiteTiles(string floor, int numCarpets, int carpetLen) {
        int n = floor.length();
        vector<int> prefix_floor;
        int count = 0;
        if(floor[0]=='1'){
            prefix_floor.push_back(1);
            count++;
        }
        else prefix_floor.push_back(1);
        for(int i=1; i<n; i++){
            if(floor[i]=='1'){
                prefix_floor.push_back(1 + prefix_floor[i-1]);
                count++;
            }
            else{
                prefix_floor.push_back(prefix_floor[i-1]);
            }
        }
        vector<vector<int>> dp(n,vector<int>(numCarpets+1,-1));
        return count-f(0,numCarpets,carpetLen,prefix_floor,floor,n,dp);
    }
};
```

