The most basic intuition we can get after seeing the problem is that , **for every index i ( 0 <= i < n )** in the array there are **2 possibilites** - 

**1. You put a carpet** 

    So if you decide to put carpet on ith block , then you don't have to worry about the indices i , i + 1 , i + 2 ... i + len - 1. (len -> is carpet length)

   This will cost you one carpet and now you have to do the same thing from index **i + len** with **numCarpet - 1** .

2. **You do not put a carpet**

	Now , if the ith tile is white this will increase the **white tile count by 1**.
	And now you have to do the same thing from index **i + 1** with **numCarpet**.

**Your answer will be the minimum of 2 cases.**

